    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Monday, 3rd of Kislev(Nov), 1865</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Only on <date>Friday</date> did I come in possession of the
                “Occident”,<lb/> and I am very thankful to you for the quite correct printing of the
                arti<lb/>cle. Nevertheless, I found mistakes in the printing and 2 which I note<lb/>
                <del>?</del> on the last of this letter which are quite serious, so that you will
                not make<lb/> the same mistakes in the <date>January</date> issue. I must again
                dispense with a note<lb/> or a judgment on your part — my health is quite affected.
                I can't work<lb/> as much anymore. Is it any wonder? Sorrow, worry,
                    <sic>andannoyances</sic> bend<lb/> me low, me, the proud man, they bend
                downward. If it is possible, I shall<lb/> send you, by the <date>20th</date>, more
                of my work with which you will not have so<lb/> much to occupy yourself.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In any event, I expect that you will translate the article<lb/>
                completely for the <date>January</date> number. Secondly, to complete the
                introduction<lb/> and send me the proof sheets betimes. I also want you
                    <sic>toprint</sic> in the<lb/>
                <del>?</del> “Occident” <sic>myarticle</sic> in the “Jewish Messenger”.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">And now a word in the open. “Open reproof is better than<lb/> love
                in secret”. Your article about the <del>?</del>, affected<lb/> me most painfully, an
                for a double reason. For I respect and love you<lb/> sincerely. First because the
                matter is <sic>criticised</sic> severely, secondly<lb/> because the people are
                right. Through such impolite means, we shall<lb/> never arrive at the goal. How is
                it possible that in a city like <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> a board should
                be organized by 33 ignoramuses,- reverends and chazanim?<lb/> Is there not the
                reform party correct when it pokes fun at the affair?<lb/> The board in
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> is fairly <del>?</del> good, especially with
                such per-<lb/>sonalities, but it, too, lacks a respectable leader. So, for God's
                sake,<lb/> you continue your old horse in relation to the reformers. One must
                com-<lb/>pletely ignore them, as if they did not exist, and stride ahead with
                re-<lb/>ligious conservative ideas, conscious of the time. Thus independence<lb/>
                will be developed. The articles must be made worthy. Would you perhaps<lb/> like to
                print, in the <date>January</date> number, my German article? If so, I will<lb/>
                send it to you, and my article will create a sensation. But I must say</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>that if you must continue my Hebrew article in the <date>January</date> issue,<lb/>
                otherwise, I must ask you to send it back to me, since I want to have it<lb/>
                printed in <placeName>Europe</placeName> in pamphlet form.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Did you <sic>forwars</sic> my letter to <persName>Jacob
                    Friedman</persName>? I have<lb/> received no answer from him. I beg of you to
                remind him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Send me 50 copies of your small catechism bound.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I call your attention to the fact that I have moved my<lb/> office
                to <placeName>117 Nassau Street, Room 10</placeName>. Please send everything
                there.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">With sincere respect,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Your loyal friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah of the house of Bondi</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I must also ask you to print my German articles either at the end or in<lb/> an
                appendix. That is to your advantage, too.</p>
        </body>
